    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-12-05T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-12-05T07:00:00-05:00" n="451"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Pan American Airways, Inc./740:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-05T12:00:00+00:00"
                            >December 5, 1929—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>361. Department’s 301, November 19, 10 a.m.<note n="49" xml:id="d451fn49">See
                        footnote 48, <ref target="#pg_607">p. 607</ref>.</note> Foreign Office
                    states that the competent authorities have now sent instructions to the <pb
                        facs="0746" n="610" xml:id="pg_610"/> Governor of Jamaica who has been
                    informed that temporary permission has been granted to Pan American Airways to
                    make a survey flight to Jamaica from Cuba with a view to examining the
                    desirability of establishing an air service to Jamaica to land, re-fuel and make
                    minor repairs on the Islands and, if awarded the contract by the United States
                    Post Office, to deliver United States mail to Jamaica. The Foreign Office adds
                    that the Governor has been instructed to issue a special and temporary
                    authorization for these purposes under article 27, (2), of the air navigation
                    (colonies, protectorates and mandated territories) order of 1927, subject to
                    such conditions as he may consider necessary to impose.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
